{"nodes": [{"id": "yt_fleet_doc", "label": "Claude Code release-roundup video: an agent fleet that runs itself (background subagents that open their own PRs), a /fork command for conversations, Claude in Chrome GA, Sonnet 5 as default with a 1M-token window, and a suite of durability fixes billed as 'the end of babysitting'.", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": "seg 1-8", "source_url": "https://youtu.be/e3rbymcXeuc", "captured_at": "2026-07-22", "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "yt_fleet_background_subagents", "label": "Subagents now run in the background BY DEFAULT and no longer block your session \u2014 they work behind it while you keep typing; up to ~200 can run at once before a cap steps in.", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": "seg 4,9,10", "source_url": "https://youtu.be/e3rbymcXeuc", "captured_at": "2026-07-22", "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "yt_fleet_auto_pr", "label": "When a background subagent completes real code work it commits, pushes, and drafts the pull request itself \u2014 you return to a commit + push + draft PR waiting for review (the headline 'agents ship their own PR' change).", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": "seg 5,12", "source_url": "https://youtu.be/e3rbymcXeuc", "captured_at": "2026-07-22", "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "yt_fleet_notification", "label": "A notification fires when a background agent finishes or needs input, so you don't have to poll the fleet.", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": "seg 10", "source_url": "https://youtu.be/e3rbymcXeuc", "captured_at": "2026-07-22", "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "yt_fleet_agents_view", "label": "The agents view shows the whole roster of running sessions; Ctrl-X cleans up finished worktrees WITHOUT losing unpushed commits.", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": "seg 11", "source_url": "https://youtu.be/e3rbymcXeuc", "captured_at": "2026-07-22", "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "yt_fleet_self_upgrade", "label": "Background agents upgrade themselves after an update lands (no manual restart to pick up a new version).", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": "seg 12", "source_url": "https://youtu.be/e3rbymcXeuc", "captured_at": "2026-07-22", "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "yt_fleet_mcp_backgrounding", "label": "MCP calls that run longer than two minutes move themselves to the background instead of blocking the session.", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": "seg 13", "source_url": "https://youtu.be/e3rbymcXeuc", "captured_at": "2026-07-22", "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "yt_fleet_session_picker", "label": "Restarting an agent opens a picker of past sessions, including ones you deleted \u2014 recover and resume prior agent work.", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": "seg 13", "source_url": "https://youtu.be/e3rbymcXeuc", "captured_at": "2026-07-22", "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "yt_fleet_fork", "label": "/fork copies your conversation into a NEW background session while the original keeps going \u2014 branch a line of work without losing your place.", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": "seg 6,22", "source_url": "https://youtu.be/e3rbymcXeuc", "captured_at": "2026-07-22", "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "yt_fleet_subtask", "label": "/subtask replaces the old in-session helper: a forked subagent that inherits your conversation context and runs the side task.", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": "seg 22", "source_url": "https://youtu.be/e3rbymcXeuc", "captured_at": "2026-07-22", "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "yt_fleet_sonnet5_1m", "label": "Sonnet 5 is the new DEFAULT model with a 1-million-token context window.", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": "seg 7", "source_url": "https://youtu.be/e3rbymcXeuc", "captured_at": "2026-07-22", "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "yt_fleet_durability_network", "label": "Durability: network drops no longer abort a turn, and transient errors are re-driven with backoff \u2014 a long run survives flaky connectivity.", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": "seg 31", "source_url": "https://youtu.be/e3rbymcXeuc", "captured_at": "2026-07-22", "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "yt_fleet_ratelimit_resume", "label": "Rate-limited subagents no longer die silently \u2014 they report the limit and RESUME when it clears (key for unattended fan-out that hits rate limits).", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": "seg 32", "source_url": "https://youtu.be/e3rbymcXeuc", "captured_at": "2026-07-22", "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "yt_fleet_session_survival", "label": "Background sessions survive a stop, a restart, even the daemon replacing itself mid-run; interrupted agents pick their work back up on their own.", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": "seg 33", "source_url": "https://youtu.be/e3rbymcXeuc", "captured_at": "2026-07-22", "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "yt_fleet_end_babysitting", "label": "Collectively these resilience fixes 'end babysitting': the overnight pipeline that used to need you at 2am now needs only a code review over coffee \u2014 the shift is from watching agents work to reviewing what they shipped.", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": "seg 30,34,35", "source_url": "https://youtu.be/e3rbymcXeuc", "captured_at": "2026-07-22", "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "yt_fleet_automode_platforms", "label": "Auto-mode now works on Bedrock, Vertex, and Foundry without opt-in; if it drifts, 'auto-mode reset' wipes the slate behind a confirmation prompt.", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": "seg 14,15", "source_url": "https://youtu.be/e3rbymcXeuc", "captured_at": "2026-07-22", "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "yt_fleet_permission_hardening", "label": "Safety hardening for more autonomy: plan mode no longer auto-runs file-modifying commands; destructive commands with unresolved variables stop and ask; the default permission mode is now honestly named 'manual'; the Agent tool is hardened against indirect prompt injection.", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": "seg 16,17,20", "source_url": "https://youtu.be/e3rbymcXeuc", "captured_at": "2026-07-22", "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "yt_fleet_rewind_past_clear", "label": "The rewind command now reaches PAST /clear, so yesterday's work isn't gone after a context reset.", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": "seg 23", "source_url": "https://youtu.be/e3rbymcXeuc", "captured_at": "2026-07-22", "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "yt_fleet_skill_stacking", "label": "You can stack up to five skills in a single line.", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": "seg 23", "source_url": "https://youtu.be/e3rbymcXeuc", "captured_at": "2026-07-22", "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "yt_fleet_streaming_efficiency", "label": "Streaming coalesces its updates, cutting processor use ~37% on long sessions; the binary also lost 7MB \u2014 efficiency gains that matter for hours-long runs.", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": "seg 8,29", "source_url": "https://youtu.be/e3rbymcXeuc", "captured_at": "2026-07-22", "author": null, "contributor": null}], "edges": [{"source": "yt_fleet_doc", "target": "yt_fleet_background_subagents", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "yt_fleet_doc", "target": "yt_fleet_auto_pr", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "yt_fleet_doc", "target": "yt_fleet_fork", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "yt_fleet_doc", "target": "yt_fleet_subtask", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "yt_fleet_doc", "target": "yt_fleet_sonnet5_1m", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "yt_fleet_doc", "target": "yt_fleet_end_babysitting", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "yt_fleet_doc", "target": "yt_fleet_automode_platforms", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "yt_fleet_doc", "target": "yt_fleet_permission_hardening", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "yt_fleet_background_subagents", "target": "yt_fleet_auto_pr", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "yt_fleet_background_subagents", "target": "yt_fleet_notification", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "yt_fleet_background_subagents", "target": "yt_fleet_agents_view", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "yt_fleet_background_subagents", "target": "yt_fleet_self_upgrade", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "yt_fleet_background_subagents", "target": "yt_fleet_mcp_backgrounding", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "yt_fleet_fork", "target": "yt_fleet_subtask", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "yt_fleet_agents_view", "target": "yt_fleet_session_picker", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "yt_fleet_end_babysitting", "target": "yt_fleet_durability_network", "relation": "rationale_for", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "yt_fleet_end_babysitting", "target": "yt_fleet_ratelimit_resume", "relation": "rationale_for", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "yt_21d5f7e6c45c.txt", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"s